bio.experienceSummary:
I am from South Africa and have been living in America, going on six years. I am a former Au pair of two years and a professional nanny of three. I have worked with families in areas of Westfield, Cranford, Roselle park, union, Maplewood NJ 

I know CPR and first aid training. I am educated on early development for infants. I know about food and nutrition for all ages. I'm educated on behavioral health of all ages. I have my own car with excellent driving records and have been driving kids around for years.


If this sounds like a good fit, I would love to chat more. Thank you for taking this time to read my background.

I've always had a passion for nurturing children and helping them grow. My journey into childcare began when I was a teenager, babysitting for various families. This experience solidified my desire to support families and provide a reliable childcare option for them.

As a caregiver, I pride myself on being patient and calm, which helps create a serene environment for the children in my care. My friendly and approachable nature allows me to build strong relationships with both children and parents. I believe open communication is key, so I ensure regular updates and follow the parents' preferred communication method to keep them informed about their child's day or any issues that arise.

With two years of experience and a deep understanding of child development, I am comfortable caring for children of all ages, from infants to preteens. I am confident in enforcing household rules and ensuring the safety and well-being of the children in my care.

Hello! I am a mother of a beautiful 12-year-old girl. I have years of paid experience with children of all ages. I hope I am the Nanny your family is looking for. 

I can help with cooking, cleaning, and laundry. I drive and I help with errands as well as pet sitting or house sitting when families are on vacation. 

I speak Spanish fluently and I speak a little Italian as well. I love to sing and I really enjoy playing outdoors. I swim and I can help with HW.

Feel free to message me at any moment. I will get back to you as soon as I can.

description.displayText: Leticia has worked with us for the last 6 months and has been great. As a house keeper, she is very detail oriented and extremely thoughtful. She organizes the house and pays attention to our preferences. As a babysitter, she was very responsible with our 2 year old, made sure she had fun and understanding of our daughters sleep routine. Would highly recommend!

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Ritila (you can also refer to me as Ritch). I'm 31 years old, and a proud mommy of 2 amazing boys. I'm currently looking for a part-time position. I'm a certified preschool teacher(CDA), and currently in school majoring in psychology. I have experience from working at a preschool facility for 5 years. I also have certificates for attending workshops, including first AID and CPR. In caring for your child; as I have learned throughout these 5 years, my first priority is to keep your child SAFE and healthy. I love caring for children and I'll respect and care for your child as if they were my own. I also have experience working with families through care. com. I will do what is necessary to meet the child and Family's needs. Thank you.

description.originalText:
Ritch worked as a nanny for my two children. From our first meeting, I knew Ritch was a catch. She disarmed my eldest son (she has a natural way with children), and comforted me with her encouraging way. 

Over the course of a year, Ritch became part of the family. Ritch has a background in preschool education, which shows through in her creative techniques, knowledge of conflict resolution, and perfectly equilibrated soft style. 

A typical day might involve dancing to the Wiggles, combining arts and crafts and learning the numbers, and a fresh and healthy snack. 

We really bonded, my kids LOVED her, and I recommend her to the highest degree. My entire family will miss her dearly.

description.originalText: Krystal is amazing. She was my daughter’s teacher at daycare from ages 2 to 3 and was so caring and loving. My daughter seemed to love her, so I decided to ask Krystal to babysit for us on the weekends. My son was only 1 at the time but instantly fell in love with her her as well, so we knew she was a perfect match for our family. Krystal can juggle meal time, bath and bedtime with ease. She is patient, kind, and trustworthy and that’s all I can really ask for in someone taking care of my babies!

bio.experienceSummary: Years of experience with kids any age ) laundry, light housekeeping, house organizing, love to cook

Hello Families,
 
My name is Miss Maya and I hold vast experience with children ranging in age, of both neurotypical and neuro divergent backgrounds in nannying and school-like settings! I truly value the trust it takes to put your child in the hands of someone else's care and always aim to build reliable and strong relationships with the families I support. As a nanny and educator, encouraging a healthy imagination, creativity and fostering whole-child development are my top priorities. I currently serve as Lead Teacher within a pre-school classroom, assisting toddler-aged children. My goal, is to bring these skills to your family and become an asset to your child's development. I am CPR, First Aid, AED, MAT and SCIP trained / certified as well. Thank you for your time and consideration.

description.originalText: Moved out of New york two years ago, but every time I come up north to visit I always reach out to Maya watch my three year old daughter.  She is just such a loving and caring person. Warm  and kind individual and is always punctual. I always appreciated the fact that she always keeps me updated - via text - with my daughter while I’m away. It’s nice to know what’s going on. She always makes me feel at ease, and ALWAYS has activities for my daughter to do  which is a plus. This is why I ALWAYS call Maya. She is extremely reliable and helpful!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there!
I am a very energetic well organized person. I am the oldest of 6 children therefore I have helped my parents with my siblings. I love working with children they bring such happiness into my life because they are all so full of life. I have nannied for three different families between 2022/24. I have cared for children as small as 3 months and as big as 10 years old. I can say I have care giving experience. What helps me out the most in care giving is the fact that I love children and I love to look out for their own well being. I am able to provide transportation when needed. I am also very crafty and like activities. I am also able to do work around the house, such as tiding up, laundry, and light meal prepping if needed. I also love pets! I am CPR and RBT certified. As well as bilingual in Spanish.

Hello, my name is Edna. I deeply enjoy working with children and have over 10 years of experience in classroom and home settings with children of all ages - infants to teenagers! I graduated from Penn State University with a BS in early childhood education and have remained in childcare since. I love being a part of people's lives at such an integral stage and it brings me joy to help and grow with families.

I'm a dedicated caregiver with a passion for nurturing and supporting children's development. With a year of experience, I've gained the knowledge and skills to provide a safe, stimulating, and nurturing environment for children of all ages, from infants to preteens. I believe in fostering a child's natural curiosity and creativity while instilling a sense of responsibility and respect.

I'm known for my patience, calmness, and friendly nature, which helps me connect with children and build trusting relationships. I keep parents informed about their child's day and any concerns that arise, using their preferred communication method.

I'm comfortable enforcing household rules as guided by the parents, and I enjoy playing a variety of games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that promote learning. Whether it's teaching them how to swim or helping them with their homework, I strive to make a positive impact on their lives.
